<p>The fundraising competition among departments of philosophy to raise funds to fight malaria, <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/12/01/philosophers-against-malaria-philosophy-department-fundraising-competition/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">launched</a> at the start of this month, has come to an end. <span id="more-56022"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-51961 aligncenter wp-dark-mode-bg-image" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3-1024x753.png" sizes="auto, (max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3-1024x753.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3-300x221.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3-768x565.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3-400x294.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/philosophers-against-malaria-3.png 1244w" alt="" width="550" height="404" /></p>
<p><a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.maltehendrickx.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Malte Hendrickx</a> (Michigan), who organizes the annual competition, says that this year it raised a total of $23,750.</p>
<p>That buys around 11,800 anti-malaria mosquito nets.</p>
<p>He also shared which philosophy departments raised the most funds:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><em><a href="https://philosophy.mit.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>MIT</strong></a> took the lead early and defended the top spot valiantly, propelled by a generous donation of suspect origin: an anonymous donation of $5000 from twin earth! Organizers are unsure what this refers to, but it sure means a lot in the fight against Malaria.Â The other podium spots went to two veteran teams from the Philosophers Against Malaria competition: the <a href="https://lsa.umich.edu/philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>University of Michigan</strong></a> and the <a href="https://www.colorado.edu/philosophy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>University of Colorado Boulder</strong></a>.</em></p>
<p>MIT raised $11,501.75.</p>
<p>You can see the full results <a href="https://www.againstmalaria.com/FundraiserGroup.aspx?FundraiserID=9418" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Thanks to Malte Hendrickx for putting together this fundraiser.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/12/29/philosophers-against-malaria-competition-results/">Philosophers Against Malaria: Competition Results</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>